<topic id="customizing_the_author_visual_editing_mode">
    <title>Customizing the Author Visual Editing Mode</title>
    <body>
        <p id="p_vxf_dgk_54b">The <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-css-support-in-author.html"
        format="html" scope="external"><b>Author</b> visual editing mode is based on CSS</xref>.
      Besides supporting most of the CSS 3 specification, <ph keyref="product"/> adds some <xref
        href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oXygen-css-extensions.html"
        format="html" scope="external">custom CSS selectors, properties, and functions</xref>.
      Customization possibilities include:</p>
        <ul id="ul_mtl_5xr_rgb">
            <li id="li_wxf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_xxf_dgk_54b">Use <xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-additional-custom-selectors.html"
            format="html" scope="external">CSS selectors</xref> to match XML comments, processing
          instructions, entities, and CDATA sections.</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_yxf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_zxf_dgk_54b">Change the tags display mode and tag color for certain elements, mark certain XML
          elements as not editable, and other customizations using <xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-css-additional-properties.html"
            format="html" scope="external">additional CSS properties</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_ayf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_byf_dgk_54b">Use <xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oxygen-css-functions.html"
            format="html" scope="external">custom CSS functions</xref>. For example, the
            <b>oxy_xpath</b> function allows you to run an XPath search over the document and use
          that value as static text.</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_cyf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_dyf_dgk_54b">In <xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-custom-css-pseudo-classes.html"
            format="html" scope="external">custom pseudo-classes</xref>, you can match values that
          can be changed via a custom action.</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_eyf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_fyf_dgk_54b">There are specific <xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-oxygen-media-type.html"
            format="html" scope="external">@media types</xref> that can be used to mark certain CSS
          sections for a certain distribution.</p>
            </li>
            <li id="li_gyf_dgk_54b">
                <p id="p_hyf_dgk_54b"><xref
            href="https://www.oxygenxml.com/doc/ug-editor/topics/dg-font-face-media.html"
            format="html" scope="external">Fonts can be dynamically loaded</xref> and used for
          rendering.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </body>
